The paper proposes a new framework for multivariate time series forecasting with missing values by jointly exploring local and global temporal dynamics. This involves leveraging memory networks and adversarial training to enhance the modeling of global temporal distribution. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers papers on the development of algorithms and models for machine learning, which is the main focus of the paper. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers papers on the development of intelligent agents and systems, which is relevant to the use of memory networks in the proposed framework. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category covers papers on the development of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms, which are relevant to the use of recurrent neural networks and adversarial training in the proposed framework. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This sub-category covers papers on the analysis and modeling of social and information networks, which may be relevant to the application domains of multivariate time series forecasting. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): This sub-category covers papers on the study of information processing and communication, which may be relevant to the use of memory networks and adversarial training in the proposed framework.
